      {
        "voice": "The suggestion correctly targets the learner’s denominator habit, but it misfires on this example: for 1/3 + 1/5, 15 is already the least common denominator. A stronger intervention would validate this case, then ask the learner to explain why 1/4 + 1/6 has a smaller shared denominator while 1/3 + 1/5 does not.",
